{"TopicId":211412,"ForumId":18,"TopicTitle":"What is -x-x","CreatedByName":"Ryaja","CreatedById":221431,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-09T22:13:35Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Ryaja","CreatedById":221431,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-09T22:13:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI thought of this question earlier and can\u0027t figure it out, it could be (-x)(-x) or (-x)-(x), so which one would it default to?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nazalassa","CreatedById":217956,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-09T22:18:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think it\u0027s (-x)-(x), for clarity you should put parenthesis if you want to say (-x)(-x).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPersonally I see a dead person with glasses \u003Cspan\u003E:D\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n-x-x\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Deddly","CreatedById":62955,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-09T22:19:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHang on... isn\u0027t the answer simply \u0022x\u0022?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(as an answer to -x-x)\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-01-09T22:20:21Z\u0022 title=\u002201/09/2023 10:20  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 9, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Deddly\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ryaja","CreatedById":221431,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-09T22:22:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224217361\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022211412\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221673302770\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002262955\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Deddly\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Deddly said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHang on... isn\u0027t the answer simply \u0022x\u0022?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(as an answer to -x-x)\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, because it is either negative x minus x which is negative two x or negative x times negative x which is x^2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-10T02:11:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224217368\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022211412\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221673302929\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022221431\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ryaja\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Ryaja said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, because it is either negative x minus x which is negative two x or negative x times negative x which is x^2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nexcept you would not write negative x times negative x that way.\u00A0 That would be\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-x(-x)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand before you say xx could be x^2 in the same way you write xy to mean x times y (x times x), and thus -x-x could also be x^2 - the conventions matter.\u00A0 -x-y would never be understood as anything but negative x minus y.\u00A0 AFAIK - you do need the parenthesis.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-10T06:03:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe reverse notation is so much better:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nx\u00B1^x-\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}